span is used to add different attributes to any words inside a <p>
span is an inline element
block-level elements take up the whole page width,while inline elements exist within those lin
es, and only take up as much of the screen as they need to
any closing block element creates a line break.
text-align can only align  block-level elements to the right.
THe best way to right-justify oinline spans is  css property float
floats let the content of a <span> or more frequently, allow to slide an image ,around inside
its container elements
 opacity
